 the importance of government regulations and policies in order to minimize the harmful effects of patenting while promoting the beneficial ones.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aBiotechnology industriesxLaw and legislationxUnited States. 0aBiotechnology industriesxLaw and legislationzUnited States. 0aHuman genomevPatentsxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aHuman genomexPatentsxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aPatent laws and legislationxUnited States. 0aPatent laws and legislationzUnited States. 0aRecombinant DNAvPatentsxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aRecombinant DNAxPatentsxMoral and ethical aspects. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 7aSCIENCE / Philosophy & Social Aspects.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791485941423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791485941/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles